<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,793,1538]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1045,1070]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Small in size (length &lt;
<number box="[621,667,1045,1070]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="550.0">550</number>
), dorsal furrow without glandularia or platelets, P 
<number box="[1262,1275,1045,1070]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="5.0">5</number>
very slender, terminal seta of IV-leg- 
<number box="[413,426,1081,1106]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="6.0">6</number>
longer than segment.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,793,1538]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1117,1142]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Description</emphasis>
. Female: Colour brownish, idiosoma 
<number box="[786,828,1117,1142]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="526.0">526</number>
(
<number box="[847,949,1117,1142]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="514.5" valueMax="527.0" valueMin="502.0">502–527</number>
) long, 
<number box="[1037,1079,1118,1142]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="227.0">227</number>
(
<number box="[1098,1200,1117,1142]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="229.0" valueMax="239.0" valueMin="219.0">219–239</number>
– 
<number box="[1215,1256,1117,1142]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="251.0">251</number>
) wide and 
<number box="[1394,1436,1117,1142]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="296.0">296</number>
(
<number box="[158,260,1154,1178]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="288.0" valueMax="292.0" valueMin="284.0">284–292</number>
) high. Dorsal furrow without glandularia or platelets. Tips of Cx-I with two stout curved setae, one short and one long. Coxal surface with a punctate pattern, near anterior margin reticulated. Genital field with three pairs of acetabula, anterior pair long and narrow, central and posterior pair gradually shorter. Posterior of genital field lies the excretory pore, but not visible in ventral view. Length/height of P 
<number box="[970,980,1261,1286]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1.0">1</number>
-P 
<number box="[1009,1024,1261,1286]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="5.0">5</number>
: 
<number box="[1034,1064,1261,1286]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="26.0">26</number>
/18, 33/18, 32/20, 
<date box="[1266,1332,1261,1286]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1941-06-16">41/16</date>
, 22/ 
<number box="[1383,1397,1261,1286]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="6.0">6</number>
. P 
<number box="[1424,1437,1262,1286]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="3.0">3</number>
with two long anterodorsal setae, P 
<number box="[545,558,1297,1322]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="5.0">5</number>
very slender. Length of IV-leg- 
<number box="[917,958,1297,1322]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
: 56, 60; terminal seta of IV-leg-6, 94 long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,793,1538]" box="[199,999,1333,1358]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Male: In all aspects similar to female. Idiosoma 
<number box="[739,781,1334,1358]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="494.0">494</number>
long and 
<number box="[893,935,1333,1358]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="263.0">263</number>
high.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,657,1369,1394]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,793,1538]" box="[199,657,1369,1394]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1369,1394]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Etymology</emphasis>
. Named for its brown colour.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,793,1538]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1405,1430]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks</emphasis>
. The new species is closest to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wiles, 1999" authorityName="Wiles" authorityYear="1999" box="[654,948,1405,1430]" class="Arachnida" family="Oxidae" genus="Oxus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lewisi">
<emphasis box="[654,784,1405,1430]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Oxus lewisi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wiles" box="[800,940,1405,1430]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="Wiles, P. R. (1999) The water mites (Acari: Hydrachnidia) of Borneo and additional new species from Thailand and Sulawesi. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 47, 409 - 439." type="journal article" year="1999">
Wiles, 
<number box="[880,940,1406,1430]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1106,1186,1405,1430]" name="Brunei" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Brunei</collectingCountry>
. With a length of 
<number box="[1387,1432,1406,1430]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="827.0">827</number>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[151,253,1441,1466]" class="Arachnida" family="Oxidae" genus="Oxus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lewisi">
<emphasis box="[151,253,1441,1466]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">O. lewisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is much larger, with larger palp and leg segments and the terminal seta of IV-leg- 
<number box="[1210,1223,1441,1466]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="6.0">6</number>
equal in length to segment.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
